		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> SMEG&#39;s Comeback 6/5/02<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.64)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=4254'>Casey "Smeg" Barson</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=4254&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> June 8, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> So I haven&#39;t played in a tournament for like almost 2 months and I&#39;m really pissed that I wasn&#39;t able to make it down to Vegas for the DPC to represent for Utah.  So needless to say I&#39;m a little ancy for a game.  I came to the weekly tournament two weeks ago but it had been canceled like the day before and nobody had bothered to send out an e-mail or nothin&#39; to let the players know.  So that also has made me a little upset.  All in all I was looking for blood at this tournament.  I was also looking also to pop the bubble of confidence that Matt Freed (#2 in the US) had iniflated over my absence.  It would be a tournament that I would either do really well at or completely flop.  I couldn&#39;t wait.<br />
<br />
I arrive at the shop about 15 min early and Hag and Tom are playing a game of Star Wars.  Not the new crappy one, the old good one.  This has to be a good sign as I haven&#39;t seen a game happening in like forever.  I get excited to play again and have since pulled out my cards to prepare for a tournament next thurs.  But I digress.  On with the games.<br />
<br />
Game 1:  Me (1837) vs. Jeff Mafi (1594)<br />
<br />
Jeff is a cool guy and really fun to play against.  We start by me winning the bid with 5 and starting the Prancing Pony.  I start Sam so I don&#39;t really have to worry about the burdens much.  I pull Aragorn: KIE and move onto site 3 with little opposition from Jeff&#39;s minions.  Jeff does the same thing, but forgot to pull Aragorn.  So now we&#39;re both sitting on site 3 and I move to 4, fortunately Jeff is playing with the same site 4 as myself.  I move and have to face a couple Moria nothings and stop (because against moria you&#39;d have to be either stupid or insane to move from 3 - 5).  When I reconsile my hand I draw almost all shadow cards.  I already have out 2 armories and now my scimitars will be very useful.  He deploys some of his elf allies and some support cards, but no other companions, just Legolas and Arwen, his start.  He moves to the Great Chasm and ends up giving me quite a bit of twilight.  I play two runners from hand, HoT for a Scavanger who pulls up a scimitar, adds 2, play a Moria Archer Troop from hand and then the Cave Troll comes out for 7.  All in all, it was then a bad day for Jeff as he tried to use Legolas to save himself, I prevented the wounds with my armories.  He tried to move his guys around so that one wouldn&#39;t die, but I knew that Frodo would los e the fierce battle with the troll so I made sure that the other two were overwhelmed and the troll did his job to Frodo on the comeback.<br />
<br />
FW  +3<br />
<br />
Highs:  I love winning a game by killing your opponents Frodo, it seems more meaningful.  Jeff for being a good sport about losing, that always is a high.<br />
Lows:  Jeff not remembering my site 1 and forgetting to pull Aragorn.  He&#39;d been playing against decks that didn&#39;t start the pony all day and so it just slipped his mind.<br />
<br />
So from what I gather all the players who should&#39;ve won, did and now the field gets a little hairy.  Since my game ended rather quickly, I decide that I need a beverage and head on out to the 7-11 for a drink. I end up getting one for Hag too and as I&#39;m coming back to the store Matt is waiting outside telling me to hurry.  I guess that means I&#39;m playing him next, why else would he care??  Excellent, this is what I was waiting for, my shot at the title.<br />
<br />
Game 3: Me vs. Matt Freed (2007)<br />
<br />
So while the rest of Utah had succumbed to Moria as our minion of choice, Matt did not believe.  He was convinced that Nazgul were the best as they were the biggest.  His rating is proof enough that its not the minion that make the rating.  So I bid 5 again and he bids 6 so he goes first.  I normally start Sam/Legolas, but after seeing his starting site is the Green Dragon, I decide it would be better to start Aragorn.  So he pulls sam and moves to site 2, having nothing else to deploy.  Since all of my minions are roaming I can only play a lowly runner who gets beaten down.  He stops to allow his hand to more balance itself.  He had an entire hand of nothing but Ringwraiths and one Servant of the Secret Fire.  So he stops, and I go.  I pull Sam and remove 3 burdens, play Barlimir for free and move.  He can only play an Ulaire Cantea against me and so Aragorn takes 2 wounds and I stop.  He moves to my site 3, the forrest. and stops again as he has yet to draw anything to play.  I do the same, not playing anything hoping that He wouldn&#39;t be able to draw anything useful before I could start to run against him.  I end up with my two Moria Archer troops in my hand as he moves into the Great Chasm.  I play a runner and then both of the Troops.  He takes 4 archery, 3 on Frodo (who&#39;s not wearing Isildur&#39;s Bane) and one on Aragorn.  Then Gandalf and Aragorn both lose their skirmishes and each take a wound.  He stops and I move to sight 4, two nazgul show up, but not enough to kill/wound me very much.  He plays some cards, no new companions though, and moves into the bridge.  I ask why he didn&#39;t glamdring, he says that if he did, then Gandalf wouldn&#39;t be able to take 2 hits from the Balrog.  Instead of playing the big guy, I see that if I can do 4 archery to him it&#39;ll kill off his companions as he isn&#39;t wearing the rare ring.  So I Host of Thousands twice for my tow Moria Archer troops and have enough left over to put out a Goblin Bowman too.  His Gandalf and Aragorn and Frodo all die to archery, before the skirmishes even happen.<br />
<br />
FW  +6<br />
<br />
Highs:  I just beat the number 2 rated player in the U.S. by killing Frodo.  It doesn&#39;t get any cooler than that.<br />
Lows:  Him getting a crappy opening hand and not getting any of his extra fellowship before site 5.  <br />
<br />
By now I&#39;m feeling pretty high as no matter what happens now, I&#39;m going to go up in my ranking.  I can&#39;t wait to play my next opponent.  The rest of the games finish up and Nathan, Hag and Tom all won their games and so now its between the four of us.  I get paired up against Hag and Nathan winds up against Tom.  All four are good players and we each have a shot at winning the tournament.  <br />
<br />
Game 4:  Me vs. Courtney Haggerty (1720)<br />
<br />
Don&#39;t be fooled by Hag&#39;s rating.  He is a really good player, its just that early on he was more into having fun as opposed to winning.  But now he&#39;s on the fast track up and he&#39;ll be hard to stop.  I was sitting next to Hag during the first game and I saw that he bid 8.  I need to go first as I saw his starting sight (call me a cheater for scouting but I was aghast at his bid).  Anyway, I bid nine to make sure I&#39;m going first.  This is nothing new for my deck, I can either work the burdens off with Aragorn: KIE/Sam or by just letting Frodo die and escort Sam to Mt. Doom.  I actually prefer to let Frodo die as it usually gets my opponent overconfident and makes him make more mistakes.  So I win, pull Aragorn, play Gandalf and we&#39;re off and running.  I lead all the way to site 6.  He&#39;s using Bilbo to get rid of my conditions and its pretty even.  I&#39;ve killed Pipen, but who doesn&#39;t just let him die when its all on the line?  On site 6 I play Elrond and the first card I draw is Thor&#39;s Map.  I play it and proceed to draw two more cards.  As I do this I see the smirk on Hags face widen, I assume at this point that he has a Tower Assassin in his hand and is planning on killing both Elrond and Barlimir.  I map for my site 7 which is discard all allies.  While this doesn&#39;t really hurt me much, it kills hobbits.  Hag can&#39;t keep up with my movement and I run into site 9 before he can.  <br />
<br />
FW  +9<br />
<br />
Highs:  Bidding nine burdens and drawing a crowdof players as we were among the last to finish.  Exerting Sam to pull Aragorn on site 1 (think about it, you&#39;ll get it eventually)<br />
Lows:  There really weren&#39;t any.  Hag is a great player and it was close up until the end.  Great game played.<br />
<br />
Between Tom and Nathan, they were both unable to play any minions to stop the other persons fellowship and since Nathan went first, he was the first one to reach site 9.  So it is down to us.  We rode in the car together here and now we&#39;re the only two undefeated players left.  But as Christopher Lambert so elequently put it, &quot;There can be only one.&quot;  So we procede to get it on.<br />
<br />
Game 4:  Me vs. Nathan Magro (1810)<br />
<br />
Nathan knows my deck backwords and forwards and I know his so we pretty much know how this game is going to turn out.  Nathan in playing a Mirror/Discard deck and even though the mirror was erratted, its still pretty effective and annoying to play against.  I bid nothing as I know his deck works on burdens and he lets me go first.  I move to site 2 and stop.  Nathan moves to my site 3 and stops, nothing eventful going on yet.  So I follow in suit and Hit hte Sanctuary and halt.  Nathan proceeds to move to site 4 where he is met by the Cave Troll and a few friends and is forced to stop,  I deploy a few and Sting nathans hand.  He has the common Balrog, 3 Hates, 2 Enduring Evils and no other minions.  I move to site 4, nothing, site 5 Balrog comes out from hand and does two wounds to Aragorn and two to Gandalf.  I sting again and find nothing.  I decide to gamble it since I don&#39;t think he&#39;s going to draw a minion to use those hates with.  My gamble paid off and I successfully move from site 3 to 6 courtesy of the Forrest site 3.  Now I&#39;m 2 sites ahead of him and its pretty smooth sailing from then on.  My site 5 he meets the Balrog and the Cave Troll again and if forced to stop.  My fellowship waltzes into site 9 from there.<br />
<br />
FW  +12<br />
<br />
Highs:  The jump from sanctuary to sanctuary.  You gotta admit, its pretty cool.<br />
Lows:  Nathan getting so annoyed at his deck he begins to throw his cards around the room.  <br />
<br />
So I end up winning the tournament.  Hag go paired up the final round against Matt and beat him too.  So much for Matts rating eh?  I end up with first, I don&#39;t know who took second as I wasn&#39;t able to stay for the award stuff.  But it was a really well run tourney and I was glad to be a part of it.  <br />
<br />
Props:<br />
<br />
Me for coming off a two month hiadis to win a tournament which involved the #2 player in the US<br />
Nathan for achieving his goal of annoying at least 4 people with his deck (this includes himself)<br />
Hag for playing in the tourney even though the deck he was playing was not his usual deck of choice. <br />
Everyone who came to make the tournament sanctioned.  We&#39;re all winners here.<br />
The mexican woman working at 7-11 for flirting with Nathan while we were getting drinks.  <br />
<br />
Slops:<br />
<br />
Matt for changing his deck right before a tournament and then testing it out with a &quot;scrub&quot;.  Losing to that scrub repeatedly, and still deciding to play with that deck.<br />
Zach for canceling the last tournament I would have attended because he had a headache.<br />
Everyone hwo didn&#39;t come for not taking the time to care about the rest of us.<br />
Nathan for getting so mad at his cards that he was throwing them everywhere, very uncool dude.<br />
Decipher for killing my game (SW:CCG) and trying to replace it with this simplistic imposter.  Thanks D!!<br />
<br />
Hope you enjoyed the read.  I&#39;m going to try to make it to the DPC in Texas as well as DPC Seattle, Denver and Comicon.  Hope to see some of you there.<br />
<br />
Casey &quot;SMEG&quot; Barson <br></font></blockquote><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php?id=3717&view=1&PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php?PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php?PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
